{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769472288,"nonce":"DB4RjmEETDCT55G8X9YSuqOrJQA=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87l95U1","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/50","origin":"github"},"title":"Enhancement: Auto-checkout to default branch after PR submission","message":"## Problem\nWhen agents submit PRs and finish a feature branch, the repository remains checked out on the feature branch. This can cause issues:\n\n- User expectations: Users expect to be back on main/default branch after work is done\n- Workflow confusion: Subsequent operations may run on wrong branch\n- Cross-agent conflicts: Multiple agents working sequentially end up on stale branches\n- Session persistence: Branch state persists across agent sessions\n\n## Current State\nThe `finish-feature` workflow documents manual checkout steps:\n```bash\ngit checkout \u003cdefault-branch\u003e\ngit pull\ngit branch -d feature/\u003ctask-id\u003e  # optional\n```\n\nHowever:\n- These steps are not automated\n- Different repositories have different default branches (main vs jazzy vs others)\n- No utility to detect default branch programmatically\n- Workflows don't enforce this cleanup\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\n1. **Create utility script** `.agent/scripts/checkout_default_branch.sh`\n   - Auto-detect default branch from origin/HEAD\n   - Checkout to default branch\n   - Pull latest changes\n   - Optional cleanup of local feature branch\n\n2. **Update workflows** to automatically call this script:\n   - `/submit-pr` workflow should checkout default branch after PR created\n   - `/finish-feature` workflow should call this script\n   - Any workflow that creates a feature branch should include cleanup\n\n3. **Update documentation**:\n   - Update `.agent/workflows/dev/submit-pr.md` to show auto-cleanup\n   - Update `.agent/workflows/dev/finish-feature.md` with new approach\n   - Document in `.agent/AGENT_ONBOARDING.md`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Utility script exists and detects default branch correctly\n- [ ] Script works for root workspace and nested repositories\n- [ ] All workflows that touch branches include cleanup step\n- [ ] Default branch auto-detection works for main, master, jazzy, and custom branches\n- [ ] Documentation updated with new automated approach\n- [ ] Tested with actual workflow execution\n\n## Related Issues\n- Issue #45: GitHub Issues as Single Source of Truth (establishes issue-first policy)\n- Issue #44: Temp File Policies (enforces workspace cleanliness)","files":null}]}